
Example Java Application.

1. Gather oracle oci driver details.
2. Create project in eclipse and ojdbc8.jar file to bild path
3. Develop the Application using Oracle oci driver.


working with Oracle thin jdbc driver


every jdbc driver is identified by its driver class name.

it is a class that implements java.sql.driver interface.

jdbc url : jdbc:oracle:thin:@<host>:<port>:<sid>
sid: service id.

Oracle thin driver details

driver class name : oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver

        or  oracle.jdbc.OracleDriver

url : jdbc:oracle:thin:@<host>:<port no>:<sid>

